Description: WOW! Fender Limited Edition American Vintage Telecaster Reclaimed Redwood + OHSC Lovies Guitars has up for grabs this amazing Fender American Vintage '50's Tele made out of Reclaimed Redwood! It's in great shape! All original in the original case! A limited edition run makes this guitar pretty rare! It's a great piece for a collector or a player! It sounds phenomenal, a nice and open tone like Teles are so good at producing! See many detailed photos included! Weighs in at 6.55lbs .813" at the 1st fret .968" at the 12th fret 1.659" Nut Width Serial: LE03021 SKU: 1586 A great guitar with a long history, and thats no small exaggeration”the body of the Limited Edition American Vintage Hot Rod 50s Tele Reclaimed Redwood is fashioned from reclaimed old-growth redwood. With antique wood reborn in musical instrument form, the versatile 50s Vintage Hot Rod design is a beauty to behold, with a humbucking neck pickup and single-coil bridge pickup for sound as compelling as the guitars look. A 4-way switch lets you choose between the combination of neck and bridge pickups in either series and parallel. Includes hardshell case.
